A. Explain #ff016b

In a RGB color space, hex #ff016b is composed of 100% red, 0.4% green 
and 42% blue. Whereas in a CMYK color space, it is composed of 0% cyan, 
99.6% magenta, 58% yellow and 0% black. It has a hue angle of 335 degrees, 
a saturation of 100% and a lightness of 50.2%. 
#ff016b color hex could be obtained by blending #ff02d6 with #ff0000. 
Closest websafe color is: #ff0066.

B. When considering a website could this color be a problem?
Yes it could be a problem because #ff016b is 
perceived by people affected by a color vision deficiency.
This can be useful if you need to ensure your color combinations 
are accessible to color-blind users.

You could use #ff0066 which is the closest websafe color to #ff016b.


